changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_1
changes.summary: Figure updated to reflect the extended safety follow-up period and Schedule of Activities changed Visit 802 to 17 weeks posttreatment period
changes.rationale: The safety follow-up period has been extended to 17 weeks to address regulatory feedback from Type C advice meeting with FDA (26 June 2019).

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_2
changes.summary: Two more interim analyses were added and text revised
changes.rationale: Additional interim analyses were requested by an external DMC to perform unblinded safety reviews semi-annually. Details pertaining to the timing of interim analyses was added.

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_3
changes.summary: Akey secondary objective was added (time to onset of T2DM during the entire study) with the associated endpoint and statistical hypothesis
changes.rationale: An additional key secondary objective was added per FDA request from Type C advice meeting with FDA (26 June 2019).

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_4
changes.summary: An appendix describing mitigation for extenuating circumstances was added as Section 10.10 Appendix 10 The Abbreviation Appendix 10 is now Appendix 11
changes.rationale: Language was added to address extenuating circumstances due to unforeseen widespread emergencies (such as pandemics or natural disasters).

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_5
changes.summary: Asentence related to selection of variance-covariance structure in case of nonconvergence was deleted
changes.rationale: The details will be provided in the Statistical Analysis Plan.

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_6
changes.summary: Allowable deviation (days) for Visit 21 was changed from +7 days to ±7 days
changes.rationale: This change allows more flexibility for participants to schedule the primary study endpoint visit.

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_7
changes.summary: Added measurement of waist circumference to Visit 199
changes.rationale: The measurement was added to obtain 3 year waist circumference data for participants who discontinue the study treatment early but come to the 3-year endpoint visit.

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_8
changes.summary: Measurement of waist circumference added to list of visit procedures
changes.rationale: The text was added to align with changes in the Schedule of Activities regarding measurement of waist circumference at Visit 199.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Continued Follow-up for Participants with Prediabetes (Visits 101 through 116)

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_9
changes.summary: Added an activity entitled 'register study visit in IWRS'
changes.rationale: The activity was added to the SOA to ensure all visits are registered. This allows monitoring of study activities using real-time IWRS reports.

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_10
changes.summary: Added text 'more than 18 months'
changes.rationale: The sentence was revised to maintain consistency with the text from the exclusion criteria.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Appendix 4 Contraceptive Guidance and Collection of Pregnancy Information

changes.name: AMEND_1_CHG_11
changes.summary: Note regarding follicle stimulating hormone levels used to confirm a postmenopausal state in women has been deleted
changes.rationale: The note could lead to misinterpretation of inclusion criterion 4.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Appendix 4 Contraceptive Guidance and Collection of Pregnancy Information

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_1
changes.summary: Key secondary objective at 20 weeks was modified, changing heading from 'by dose' to 'pooled dose' analysis, and editing objective to reflect the pooled 10 mg and 15 mg doses.
changes.rationale: Analysis of pooled data from participants on different tirzepatide doses is more appropriate as participants randomized to the 15-mg dose of tirzepatide will not be exposed to that dose until after Week 20.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_2
changes.summary: Key secondary objective at 72 weeks, by dose analysis, was modified:

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_3
changes.summary: For the body weight objective, added the endpoint '≥20% body weight reduction from randomization'.
changes.rationale: To better inform clinical decisions in management of people living with obesity.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_4
changes.summary: Deleted the objective and associated endpoint for SF-36v2 acute form Physical Functioning domain score for 10 mg and 15 mg separately.
changes.rationale: Objective and associated endpoint were moved to Key secondary at 72 weeks, pooled dose analysis.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_5
changes.summary: Revised key secondary objective at 72 weeks from 'by dose' to 'pooled dose' analysis to demonstrate that the pooled 10 mg and 15 mg QWtirzepatide is superior to placebo for SF- 36v2 acute form Physical Functioning domain score.
changes.rationale: To reduce the number of key secondary objectives.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_6
changes.summary: In the key secondary objective at 72 weeks, pooled dose analysis for tirzepatide (all doses combined) to demonstrate superiority to placebo for lipid parameters, the endpoint was modified to replace 'LDL' with 'non-HDL cholesterol', and to replace 'total' with 'HDL' cholesterol.
changes.rationale: Emerging science indicates assessing HDL- cholesterol in addition to non-HDL cholesterol should provide more valuable data on CVD risk in this specific population.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_7
changes.summary: Additional secondary objective at 72 weeks, pooled dose analysis, the endpoint associated with lipid parameters was modified to replace 'HDL' with 'LDL' cholesterol, and to add 'total cholesterol'.
changes.rationale: For consistency and to reflect the changes to the key secondary objectives.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_8
changes.summary: Added wording 'unless diabetes had been diagnosed prior to the visits'.
changes.rationale: For clarity.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Additional 2-Year Treatment Period for Participants with Prediabetes at Randomization (Visits 101 through 116)

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_9
changes.summary: Added wording regarding use of OGTT for confirming diagnosis of diabetes.
changes.rationale: For clarity and consistency with new text related to confirmation of diabetes diagnosis in Section 4.1.2.3.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_10
changes.summary: Revised definition of incident diabetes and added subsections containing clarifying information related to 'Confirmation of diabetes diagnosis' and 'Recording of incident diabetes events'.
changes.rationale: Definition of incident diabetes was revised to clarify the criteria regarding the requirement for 2 abnormal test results to confirm the diagnosis.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Definition and Management of Incident Diabetes

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_11
changes.summary: Added sentence allowing dose modification for management of participants with perceived excessive weight loss during the additional 2- year treatment period for participants with prediabetes at randomization.
changes.rationale: To support patient management and retention in the additional 2-year treatment period.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_12
changes.summary: Added this subsection containing information for managing participants with perceived excessive weight loss during the additional 2- year treatment period for participants with prediabetes at randomization.
changes.rationale: Provide clear, detailed information for managing and retaining participants in the additional 2-year treatment period.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Management of Participants with Perceived Excessive Weight Loss During the Additional 2-year Treatment Period for Participants with Prediabetes

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_13
changes.summary: Added bullet point 'Female participants will be withdrawn from the study if the participant becomes pregnant.'
changes.rationale: For clarity in participant management.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Participant Discontinuation/ Withdrawal from the Study

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_14
changes.summary: Updated to reflect the changes specified in the key secondary objectives and endpoints in Section 3.
changes.rationale: For consistency.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_15
changes.summary: Updated information on estimands and related analyses.
changes.rationale: To address and align with FDA feedback.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_16
changes.summary: Updated to reflect the changes specified in the key objectives and endpoints in Section 3.
changes.rationale: For consistency.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_17
changes.summary: Updated to replace current information with 'To identify AE terms suggestive of potential abuse liability, narrow terms fromSMQ of Drug abuse and dependence (20000101) will be used.'
changes.rationale: Based on mechanism of action of tirzepatide, anticipated gastrointestinal adverse events, and low likelihood for abuse potential/psychoactive effects, it is reasonable to narrow the list of abuse terms used.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Events Related to Potential Abuse Liability

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_18
changes.summary: Added wording pertaining to adjudication of incident diabetes events and cross-reference to related details in Section 4.1.2.3.
changes.rationale: For clarity and consistency.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_19
changes.summary: In subsection for 'Female Participants who become pregnant', modified final sentence to indicate that if a study participant becomes pregnant, the participant will discontinue study intervention 'and' will be withdrawn from the study.
changes.rationale: For clarity and to align with other changes in protocol Section 7.2.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Appendix 4 Contraceptive Guidance and Collection of Pregnancy Information"

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_20
changes.summary: Added note in the text stating that placement of a venous cannula may not be required when a 2-hour OGTT is repeated to confirm the diagnosis of diabetes during the study, and only samples at 0 and 120 minutes for glucose measurement will be collected.
changes.rationale: For clarity and to align with changes in Section 4.1.2.2.

changedSections.sectionTitle: Appendix 7 ProtocolGPHK Standardized Protocols for the Measurement of Height; Weight; Waist Circumference; Vital Signs; Electrocardiogram; and Oral

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_21
changes.summary: Used the term 'additional 2-year treatment period for participants with prediabetes at randomization' to replace similar but inconsistently used terms when referring to the study period following primary outcome at Visit 21 (Week 72).
changes.rationale: For clarity and consistency.

changes.name: AMEND_2_CHG_22
changes.summary: Minor, editorial and document formatting revisions.
changes.rationale: Minor, therefore have not been summarized.

conditions.name: COND1
conditions.label: Fasting
conditions.text: On all office visits, study participants should be reminded to report to the site before taking study drug (s) in a fasting condition, after a period of approximately 8 hours without eating, drinking (except water), or any significant physical activity. Since some screening procedures need to be completed in the fasting state, Visit 1 may be conducted over more than 1 day to ensure necessary conditions are met.

conditions.name: COND2
conditions.label: ECG for Weeks 0 and 36
conditions.text: ECGs will be performed in triplicate at Weeks 0 and 36. All other ECGs will be single measurements.

conditions.name: COND3
conditions.label: Diary training
conditions.description: Diary instruction re subject training condition
conditions.text: All training should be repeated as needed to ensure participant compliance.

conditions.name: COND4
conditions.label: Weight measurements
conditions.text: Weight measurements should be obtained per the instructions in Section 10.7. Body weight must be measured in fasting state. If the participant is not fasting, the participant should be called in for a new visit within the visit window to have the fasting body weight measured.

conditions.name: COND5
conditions.label: Diary review
conditions.text: Data from diary, as well as study drug compliance, should be reviewed

conditions.name: COND6
conditions.label: Lifestyle program
conditions.text: Counselling on diet and exercise, to be performed by a dietician or equivalent qualified delegate, to include calculation of individualized energy requirement and methods to change dietary composition and amount of physical activity ‘The Lifestyle Program Instruction may be delivered on a separate day from the rest of that visit’s study procedures but must occur within the visit window.

conditions.name: COND7
conditions.label: Lifestyle program week 8
conditions.text: Beginning at Week 8, the Lifestyle Program Instruction may be delivered by phone.

conditions.name: COND8
conditions.label: Patient compliance training
conditions.text: All training should be repeated as needed to ensure participant compliance. Study personnel to provide reinforcement and encouragement for lifestyle modifications.

conditions.name: COND9
conditions.label: Autoinjector training
conditions.description: Injection training with Autoinjector demonstration device
conditions.text: All training should be repeated as needed to ensure participant compliance

conditions.name: COND10
conditions.label: OGTT diabetes diagnosis
conditions.text: 2-hour OGTT testing should be omitted at visits following a protocol-defined diabetes diagnosis.

conditions.name: COND11
conditions.label: eGFR Reporting
conditions.text: The CKD-EPI equation will be used by the central lab to estimate and report eGFR.

conditions.name: COND12
conditions.label: C-SSRS (Baseline/Screening) administration
conditions.text: The C-SSRS, Self-Harm Supplement Form and PHQ-9 should be administered after assessment of adverse events. For this study, the C-SSRS is adapted for the assessment of the ideation and behavior categories only. The Intensity of Ideation and Lethality of Behavior sections are removed.

conditions.name: COND13
conditions.label: C-SSRS (Baseline/Screening) notes
conditions.text: For this study, the C-SSRS is adapted for the assessment of the ideation and behavior categories only. The Intensity of Ideation and Lethality of Behavior sections are removed.

conditions.name: COND14
conditions.label: Self-Harm Follow-up Form trigger
conditions.description: Self-Harm Follow-up Form required if triggered by Self-Harm Supplement Form
conditions.text: Self-Harm Follow-up Form is only required if triggered by the Self-Harm Supplement Form, per instructions in the form.
